# MarineTime — Cursor Rules

## Role
You are a senior full-stack developer working on MarineTime, a GPS-verified field attendance and timesheet PWA for marine operations. Workers are field workers on ships, docks, dry-dock yards, and offshore platforms. App runs on Android phones and shared tablets with unreliable connectivity.

## Stack
Next.js 14 App Router, TypeScript strict, Supabase (Postgres + Auth + Storage + RLS), Tailwind CSS (dark mode class strategy), idb (IndexedDB), bcryptjs, zod, papaparse, jspdf, Playwright, Vitest.

## File Structure Rules
- Route groups: (worker), (supervisor), (admin) — parentheses are Next.js grouping, not URL paths
- API routes live in src/app/api/ only
- Supabase server client (server.ts): API routes + server components
- Supabase browser client (client.ts): 'use client' components ONLY
- Migrations: supabase/migrations/ numbered 001_, 002_, etc.

## TypeScript Rules
- Strict mode — no implicit any
- Explicit return types on all exported functions
- Derive types from zod schemas: type X = z.infer<typeof schema>
- No non-null assertions without explaining why safe

## Marine Domain Rules
- Work locations are "sites" not "offices"
- Project codes: [TYPE]-[NAME]-[YEAR] e.g. BERTH-MAINT-2024
- Sub-project codes are internal task codes: PAINT-HULL, WELD-KEEL
- GPS accuracy at marine sites: 5-15m on Android. Minimum geofence radius: 50m.
- Shared tablet kiosk mode must always work — never require personal phone
- Every user action must handle offline gracefully

## GPS Rules
- Call navigator.geolocation.getCurrentPosition ONLY on explicit user tap
- Always: { enableHighAccuracy: true, timeout: 10000, maximumAge: 0 }
- Never poll GPS on a timer or interval
- Never log GPS coordinates to console or localStorage
- Server-side geofence validation is mandatory — client-side is display-only
- Always use haversineMeters() from src/lib/haversine.ts — never reimplement inline

## Photo Rules
- Camera capture always optional — Skip must be visible without scrolling
- facingMode: 'user' for selfie
- Never store base64 photo in IndexedDB
- Always private Supabase Storage bucket
- Always signed URLs with 604800s expiry

## API Route Rules
- Every route must start with: const { data: { user }, error } = await supabase.auth.getUser()
- Return 401 immediately if error or !user
- Every route must zod.parse() body before any DB operation
- Return consistent: { data: T } on success, { error: string, code?: string } on failure
- HTTP codes: 400 bad input, 401 unauthenticated, 403 forbidden, 409 conflict

## Mobile-First / Field Worker UI Rules
- Minimum touch target: 48x48px — min-h-12 min-w-12 in Tailwind
- Minimum font: text-lg (18px) body, text-2xl primary actions
- High contrast: bg-slate-900 backgrounds, white text for worker screens
- Primary action buttons: full width, sky-500 or emerald-500
- Loading states: always show spinner — field workers panic if UI freezes
- Error messages: specific — "You are 234m from Main Berth. Maximum is 75m." not "Location error."
- Offline indicator: always visible yellow banner when navigator.onLine === false

## Security Rules
- SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY: server files only
- No PII in URL query parameters
- Consent screen required before first GPS capture
- Signed URLs for photos — check expiry in display components

## Offline / PWA Rules
- All IndexedDB via idb library — never raw IndexedDB API
- Import idb dynamically: const { openDB } = await import('idb')
- Queue sync fires on window 'online' event and on app start if queue non-empty
- Show queue depth: "2 records pending sync"
- manifest.json start_url: /clock

## Testing Rules
- GPS tests: mock navigator.geolocation in beforeEach
- Camera tests: mock navigator.mediaDevices.getUserMedia
- Offline tests: control navigator.onLine via page.evaluate
- Unit test haversine.ts with known coordinate pairs

## Anti-Patterns — Never Do These
- Never fetch('/api/...') from a server component
- Never store auth tokens in localStorage
- Never call navigator.geolocation outside a user event handler
- Never create a public Supabase Storage bucket for photos
- Never implement geofence validation only on the client
- Never allow clock-in without project selection
- Never use alert() or confirm()
- Never hardcode Supabase URLs or keys in source
